1) Use the command 'pwd' to check the working directory. If not in the home directory, then use the command 'cd ..'

2) Now use the command 'mkdir' followed by a space then 'unixtest'. It should look like this: mkrdir unixtest

3) Now use the 'cd' command fdllowed by 'unixtest' to move into it. It should look like this: cd unixtest

4) Now use the 'mkdir' command followed by 'test'. It should look like this: mkdir test

5) Now use 'cd ..' to go back to the home directory. Now 'cd unixtest'. Then 'cd test'

All done!